{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0137h5kSv6ivwKN47x1HRNxv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-4: Fix ~40 TS Compilation Errors in Test Files\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `npx tsc --noEmit` to produce zero errors,\n     9→So that type safety is enforced across the entire codebase.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `npx tsc --noEmit` is run, when it completes, then zero compilation errors (down from ~40) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given the fixes, when inspected, then they're type annotation changes only -- no logic changes <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→This is a pure type-fixing story. No runtime behavior changes.\n    19→\n    20→The ~40 compilation errors are primarily in test files (`__tests__/**/*.test.ts`). Common patterns:\n    21→\n    22→1. **Missing type assertions on mocks**: `vi.fn()` returns `Mock` but callers pass it where a typed function is expected. Fix with `as unknown as TypeName` or proper `vi.fn<[], ReturnType>()` generics.\n    23→\n    24→2. **Partial object assertions**: Tests create partial objects to pass as arguments but TypeScript requires all fields. Fix with `Partial<Type>` casts or builder functions from story 12-4.\n    25→\n    26→3. **`Record<string, unknown>` looseness**: 155 `Record<string, unknown>` casts that erode type safety. Fix the most egregious ones where the actual type is known. Not all 155 need fixing in this story -- focus on the ones causing compilation errors.\n    27→\n    28→4. **Missing imports**: Some test files reference types that aren't imported. Add missing imports.\n    29→\n    30→5. **Stale type references**: After previous refactors, some tests reference types/functions that moved or were renamed. Update references.\n    31→\n    32→### Approach\n    33→\n    34→1. Run `npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | head -100` to get the full error list\n    35→2. Categorize errors by type (missing types, wrong args, stale references)\n    36→3. Fix in batches: type annotations first, then mock typing, then stale references\n    37→4. Verify with `npx tsc --noEmit` after each batch\n    38→5. Run `npm test` to confirm no runtime regressions\n    39→\n    40→### Constraint\n    41→\n    42→AC2 is critical: these must be type-only changes. If a type fix requires a logic change, that's a separate bug fix -- do not mix concerns.\n    43→\n    44→## Files to Change\n    45→\n    46→- `src/**/__tests__/*.test.ts` — Fix type annotations, add missing type imports, correct mock typing (~40 files with errors)\n    47→- `src/types/*.ts` — May need to export additional types that tests reference\n    48→- `tsconfig.json` — Verify `strict` mode settings, ensure test files are included in compilation\n    49→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016ykHKTSEDWRThUCqSkmUSn","session_id":"ff429d75-7a8f-4551-b5e9-f4da09d39b92","uuid":"dccf897b-70d4-4ec4-a0a1-2b7cbaf04f65","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:51:40.003Z"}
