{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BWLLFaSnA6WanaAjgJKdW6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-3: Template Migration -- All Templates to Static Files\n     2→\n     3→## Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\n     9→So that there's one template system.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories, when inspected, then they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given `src/templates/` TypeScript generators, when migration completes, then they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC3: Given `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`, when called, then it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 9 (Template Unification).** Two parallel template systems -> one.\n    20→\n    21→### Target Template Structure (from architecture-v3.md)\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→templates/\n    25→  dockerfiles/\n    26→    Dockerfile.nodejs           # Was nodejsTemplate() in src/templates/*.ts\n    27→    Dockerfile.python\n    28→    Dockerfile.rust\n    29→    Dockerfile.generic\n    30→    Dockerfile.verify           # Node.js verification\n    31→    Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    32→    Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl # Template with {{STAGES}} and {{COPIES}} placeholders\n    33→  otlp/\n    34→    nodejs.md\n    35→    python.md\n    36→    rust.md\n    37→  compose/\n    38→    victoria.yml\n    39→    elk.yml\n    40→    otel-collector-config.yaml\n    41→  prompts/\n    42→    ralph-prompt.md             # Was src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts\n    43→    verify-prompt.md            # Was src/templates/verify-prompt.ts\n    44→    showboat-template.md        # Was src/templates/showboat-template.ts\n    45→  docs/\n    46→    readme.md.tmpl              # Was src/templates/readme.ts\n    47→    agents.md.tmpl              # Was generateAgentsMdContent()\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→### renderTemplate() Function\n    51→\n    52→From architecture-v3.md, in `src/lib/templates.ts`:\n    53→\n    54→```typescript\n    55→function renderTemplate(templatePath: string, vars: Record<string, string>): string {\n    56→  let content = readFileSync(templatePath, 'utf-8');\n    57→  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(vars)) {\n    58→    content = content.replaceAll(`{{${key}}}`, value);\n    59→  }\n    60→  return content;\n    61→}\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→Simple `{{var}}` interpolation. No template engine dependency. No complex logic in templates -- callers compute values and pass them.\n    65→\n    66→### Migration Steps\n    67→\n    68→For each file in `src/templates/`:\n    69→1. Extract the template string from the TypeScript function\n    70→2. Replace dynamic parts with `{{VARIABLE_NAME}}` placeholders\n    71→3. Write as static file in `templates/`\n    72→4. Replace the TS function with a `renderTemplate()` call\n    73→5. Write a comparison test that verifies identical output\n    74→\n    75→Current TypeScript template files to migrate:\n    76→- `src/templates/docker-compose.ts` -> `templates/compose/`\n    77→- `src/templates/otel-config.ts` -> `templates/compose/otel-collector-config.yaml`\n    78→- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` -> `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md`\n    79→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` -> `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md`\n    80→- `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` -> `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md`\n    81→- `src/templates/readme.ts` -> `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl`\n    82→- `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` -> evaluate if this is truly a template or code generation\n    83→\n    84→`src/lib/templates.ts` already exists at 50 lines. Add `renderTemplate()` there.\n    85→\n    86→### Multi-stage Dockerfile\n    87→\n    88→`Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` uses `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}` placeholders. The caller composes build stages from per-stack templates:\n    89→\n    90→```typescript\n    91→const stages = stacks.map(s => getStackProvider(s).getDockerBuildStage()).join('\\n\\n');\n    92→const copies = stacks.map(s => getStackProvider(s).getRuntimeCopyDirectives()).join('\\n');\n    93→const dockerfile = renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl', {\n    94→  BUILD_STAGES: stages,\n    95→  COPY_DIRECTIVES: copies,\n    96→});\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→## Files to Change\n   100→\n   101→- `src/lib/templates.ts` — Add `renderTemplate(path, vars)` function\n   102→- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs` — Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   103→- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.python` — Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   104→- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.rust` — Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   105→- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` — Create. With `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}`\n   106→- `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md` — Create. Extract from `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts`\n   107→- `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md` — Create. Extract from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`\n   108→- `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md` — Create. Extract from `src/templates/showboat-template.ts`\n   109→- `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl` — Create. Extract from `src/templates/readme.ts`\n   110→- `templates/compose/victoria.yml` — Create or move from existing location\n   111→- `templates/compose/elk.yml` — Create. ELK stack compose\n   112→- `templates/compose/otel-collector-config.yaml` — Create. Extract from `src/templates/otel-config.ts`\n   113→- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   114→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   115→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   116→- `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   117→- `src/templates/docker-compose.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   118→- `src/templates/otel-config.ts` — Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016ykHKTSEDWRThUCqSkmUSn","session_id":"ff429d75-7a8f-4551-b5e9-f4da09d39b92","uuid":"a9e654c8-843c-4a81-b779-03565671a883","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:51:48.365Z"}
