{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Je7nn52hAjdzqbcs1R7k2w","type":"tool_result","content":"   480→**When** it finds `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n   481→**Then** the test fails\n   482→\n   483→**Given** a boundary test scans module imports\n   484→**When** a module imports from another module's internal file (not index.ts)\n   485→**Then** the test fails\n   486→\n   487→### Story 15-3: Template migration — all templates to static files\n   488→\n   489→As a developer,\n   490→I want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\n   491→So that there's one template system.\n   492→\n   493→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   494→\n   495→**Given** `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories\n   496→**When** inspected\n   497→**Then** they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts`\n   498→\n   499→**Given** `src/templates/` TypeScript generators\n   500→**When** migration completes\n   501→**Then** they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/`\n   502→\n   503→**Given** `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`\n   504→**When** called\n   505→**Then** it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function\n   506→\n   507→### Story 15-4: Fix ~40 TS compilation errors in test files\n   508→\n   509→As a developer,\n   510→I want `npx tsc --noEmit` to produce zero errors,\n   511→So that type safety is enforced across the entire codebase.\n   512→\n   513→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   514→\n   515→**Given** `npx tsc --noEmit` is run\n   516→**When** it completes\n   517→**Then** zero compilation errors (down from ~40)\n   518→\n   519→**Given** the fixes\n   520→**When** inspected\n   521→**Then** they're type annotation changes only — no logic changes\n   522→\n   523→### Story 15-5: Lint rule for bare exception swallowing\n   524→\n   525→As a developer,\n   526→I want code review to flag `except Exception: pass` (Python) and empty catch blocks,\n   527→So that error swallowing doesn't cause silent production incidents.\n   528→\n   529→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   530→\n   531→**Given** code-review subagent reviews Python code\n   532→**When** it finds `except Exception: pass`\n   533→**Then** it flags it as HIGH severity\n   534→\n   535→**Given** `post-write-check.sh` hook runs after writing a Python file\n   536→**When** the file contains `except Exception: pass`\n   537→**Then** it prints a warning\n   538→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016ykHKTSEDWRThUCqSkmUSn","session_id":"ff429d75-7a8f-4551-b5e9-f4da09d39b92","uuid":"30cae1f1-39c2-4061-b1b8-c32474cbb78d","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:51:57.547Z"}
