{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wi1tHBMCkmc1AcnxuvACi4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-4: Fix TS Compilation Errors Across Codebase\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `npx tsc --noEmit` to produce zero errors,\n     9→So that type safety is enforced across the entire codebase.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `npx tsc --noEmit` is run, when it completes, then zero compilation errors (down from 106 across 20 files) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given the fixes, when inspected via `git diff --stat`, then changes are limited to type annotations, type imports, and type casts -- no logic changes <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given `npm test` is run after all fixes, when it completes, then all existing tests pass with no regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given test files with partial mock objects (TS2352, TS2353), when fixed, then they use `as unknown as TypeName` double-cast or `Partial<Type>` -- not `any` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Given source files with errors (`src/commands/run.ts`, `src/lib/state.ts`, `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts`, `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts`), when fixed, then their fixes are type-only and do not change runtime behavior <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Technical Notes\n    20→\n    21→This is a pure type-fixing story. No runtime behavior changes.\n    22→\n    23→### Current Error Inventory (as of 2026-03-25)\n    24→\n    25→**106 compilation errors** across **20 files** (16 test files + 4 source files).\n    26→\n    27→#### Error breakdown by code\n    28→\n    29→| Error Code | Count | Description |\n    30→|-----------|-------|-------------|\n    31→| TS2352 | 18 | Conversion may be a mistake (partial mocks) |\n    32→| TS7006 | 16 | Parameter implicitly has 'any' type |\n    33→| TS2339 | 16 | Property does not exist on type |\n    34→| TS2353 | 15 | Object literal may only specify known properties |\n    35→| TS2741 | 12 | Property missing in type but required |\n    36→| TS2322 | 9 | Type not assignable |\n    37→| TS2556 | 8 | Spread argument must have tuple type |\n    38→| TS2345 | 8 | Argument type not assignable |\n    39→| TS2561 | 2 | Object literal property not assignable |\n    40→| TS2493 | 1 | Tuple element access error |\n    41→| TS18048 | 1 | Possibly undefined |\n    42→\n    43→#### Affected test files (16)\n    44→\n    45→- `src/commands/__tests__/bridge.test.ts`\n    46→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n    47→- `src/commands/__tests__/stack.test.ts`\n    48→- `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts`\n    49→- `src/commands/__tests__/sync.test.ts`\n    50→- `src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts`\n    51→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`\n    52→- `src/lib/__tests__/scan-cache.test.ts`\n    53→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/registry.test.ts`\n    54→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/types.test.ts`\n    55→- `src/lib/observability/__tests__/otlp.test.ts`\n    56→- `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts`\n    57→- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/timeout.test.ts`\n    58→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-docker-check.test.ts`\n    59→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts`\n    60→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts`\n    61→\n    62→#### Affected source files (4)\n    63→\n    64→- `src/commands/run.ts`\n    65→- `src/lib/state.ts`\n    66→- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts`\n    67→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts`\n    68→\n    69→### Common Fix Patterns\n    70→\n    71→1. **TS2352/TS2353 — Partial mock objects**: Tests create partial objects to pass as arguments but TypeScript requires all fields. Fix with `as unknown as TypeName` double-cast or builder functions from story 12-4. Do NOT use `as any`.\n    72→\n    73→2. **TS7006 — Implicit any on parameters**: Add explicit type annotations to callback parameters in test code (e.g., `.mockImplementation((arg: string) => ...)`).\n    74→\n    75→3. **TS2339 — Property does not exist**: Usually stale references after refactors. Update to current property names or add missing type imports.\n    76→\n    77→4. **TS2741 — Missing required properties**: Mock objects missing fields. Add the missing fields or use `Partial<Type>` with appropriate casting.\n    78→\n    79→5. **TS2322/TS2345 — Type mismatch**: Wrong types passed to functions. Correct the type annotations or add explicit casts.\n    80→\n    81→6. **TS2556 — Spread argument issues**: Spread of non-tuple types. Fix with `as const` or explicit tuple typing.\n    82→\n    83→### Approach\n    84→\n    85→1. Run `npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1` to get the full error list\n    86→2. Fix source files first (4 files, likely fewer errors, higher impact)\n    87→3. Fix test files by error category: TS2352/TS2353 first (33 errors), then TS7006 (16), then remaining\n    88→4. Verify with `npx tsc --noEmit` after each batch\n    89→5. Run `npm test` to confirm no runtime regressions\n    90→\n    91→### Constraint\n    92→\n    93→AC2 is critical: these must be type-only changes. If a type fix requires a logic change, that's a separate bug fix -- do not mix concerns.\n    94→\n    95→## Files to Change\n    96→\n    97→- `src/commands/__tests__/bridge.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n    98→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n    99→- `src/commands/__tests__/stack.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   100→- `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   101→- `src/commands/__tests__/sync.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   102→- `src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   103→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   104→- `src/lib/__tests__/scan-cache.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   105→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/registry.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   106→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/types.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   107→- `src/lib/observability/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   108→- `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   109→- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/timeout.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   110→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-docker-check.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   111→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   112→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts` — Fix type annotations and mock typing\n   113→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Fix type errors (type-only changes)\n   114→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Fix type errors (type-only changes)\n   115→- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — Fix type errors (type-only changes)\n   116→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — Fix type errors (type-only changes)\n   117→- `src/types/*.ts` — May need to export additional types that tests reference\n   118→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WkMxZtPiPNmfZs5KGPn8sb","session_id":"ff429d75-7a8f-4551-b5e9-f4da09d39b92","uuid":"f9698e1e-71f7-4985-917a-892434b69e18","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:54:37.423Z"}
