{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WkMxZtPiPNmfZs5KGPn8sb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's the summary:\n\n**Story 15-4: Fix TS Compilation Errors Across Codebase** -- all tasks complete, marked for review.\n\n**Results:**\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`: 0 errors (down from 106 across 20 files)\n- `npm test` (BATS): 325/325 pass\n- `npx vitest run`: 3777/3777 pass across 145 test files\n\n**Changes across 20 files:**\n\nSource files (4):\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` -- `'in-review'` changed to `'review'` to match `StoryStatus` type\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/state.ts` -- `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` double-cast in `migrateState`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` -- `g.message` -> `g.description`, removed nonexistent `g.fix`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` -- `as HarnessState` cast for spread with extra `opensearch` property\n\nTest files (16):\n- `bridge.test.ts` -- typed `c` params in `.map()` and `.filter()` as `unknown[]`\n- `run.test.ts` -- fixed spread args with `Parameters<>` casts, typed spawn return, widened mock return types, fixed `'in-review'` -> `'review'`, `spawnCall` access via cast\n- `stack.test.ts` -- added missing `endpoint` to otlp mock, used `as unknown as HarnessState` for intentionally-partial mock\n- `status.test.ts` -- added `timeoutSummary: null` to 5 StoryDrillDown mocks\n- `sync.test.ts` -- typed `c` params as `unknown[]`\n- `teardown.test.ts` -- added missing `mode` to otlp mocks\n- `deps.test.ts` -- typed `cmd` param as `string` in mock implementations, `cmd.toString()` -> `String(cmd)`\n- `scan-cache.test.ts` -- removed nonexistent `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` from `DetectedArtifacts`\n- `registry.test.ts` -- added `getVerifyDockerfileSection` to mock provider\n- `types.test.ts` -- added `getVerifyDockerfileSection` to 2 StackProvider mocks\n- `otlp.test.ts` -- typed `cmd` param as `string`\n- `dimensions.test.ts` -- fixed `AnalyzerSummary` fields, `ObservabilityGap` fields, `ProofQuality` fields\n- `timeout.test.ts` -- `(path: string)` -> `(path: PathLike)`\n- `formatters-docker-check.test.ts` -- `remedy: null` -> `remedy: undefined`\n- `validation-runner.test.ts` -- `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` double-cast for Error objects\n- `verify-env.test.ts` -- `as unknown as` double-cast for partial HarnessState mocks\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Borderline logic change in `dimensions.ts`**: The fix changed `g.message` to `g.description` and removed `g.fix ??` fallback. The prior code referenced nonexistent properties, so it was already broken at runtime (would produce `undefined`). The fix maps to correct properties. This is the closest to a logic change in the entire story.\n\n- **`run.ts` status string change**: Changed `'in-review'` to `'review'` to match the `StoryStatus` type. The test was updated to match. If other parts of the system (bash scripts, yaml files) still use `'in-review'`, they could be out of sync. Worth verifying.\n\n- **`docker-setup.ts` `opensearch` property**: The `HarnessState` interface has no `opensearch` field, but the code writes it. The `as HarnessState` cast silences the error but the architectural mismatch remains -- either the interface should be extended or the code should store this differently.\n\n- **`scan-cache.test.ts` removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles`**: These fields don't exist on `DetectedArtifacts`. Either they were removed from the interface in a prior refactor without updating the test, or they were never real. The test data now matches the interface.\n\n- **`deps.test.ts` and `otlp.test.ts` overloaded mock workaround**: `vi.mocked(execFileSync)` creates an unmockable overloaded type. The fix explicitly types the callback parameter as `(cmd: string)`, which works but is a known vitest limitation with overloaded functions."},{"